Patient: How can I exercise with heart failure?

Healthcare Educator: You can try chair yoga or low-impact aerobics. It's safe and you can do it at home. 

Patient: I don't know much about yoga. 

Healthcare Educator: No worries. There are online classes. Start slow and increase your pace gradually. 

Patient: What about weight training? 

Healthcare Educator: Yes, you can use small hand weights. It's good for strength and can be done at home. 

Patient: I'm worried about overdoing it. 

Healthcare Educator: Always listen to your body. If you feel tired or out of breath, take a break. 

Patient: And this will help my heart?

Healthcare Educator: Yes, regular exercise can improve your heart function and reduce symptoms. It's very beneficial.